ul.li:
A JSON object, of the form:
{"type": "typeName" ...attributes...}
where typeName is either a primitive or derived type name, as defined below. Attributes not defined in this document are permitted as metadata, but must not affect the format of serialized data.

section.source:
{
  "type": "record", 
  "name": "LongList",
  "fields" : [
    {"name": "value", "type": "long"},             // each element has a long
    {"name": "next", "type": ["LongList", "null"]} // optional next element
  ]
}

ul.li:
a request, a list of named,
	    typed parameter schemas (this has the same form
	    as the fields of a record declaration);

a one-byte error flag boolean, followed by either:


if the error flag is false, the message response,
		serialized per the message's response schema.

if the error flag is true, the error,
	      serialized per the message's error union schema.
